sudo apt install docker
docker (check the commands)
systemctl enable docker
systemctl start docker
systemctl status docker (check if it's active)
docker run [OPTIONS] IMAGE [COMMAND] [ARG...]
(sudo) docker run -it ubuntu bash (create a container with image 'ubuntu')
docker ps -a (to see all the containers, even the ones not working)
docker ps (see al the running containers)
docker rm id (of the container you want to delete)
